    "# Notebook 6 — Confidence Calibration\n",
    "**RSNA Intracranial Hemorrhage Detection**\n",
    "\n",
    "A well-calibrated model outputs probabilities that match empirical frequencies.\n",
    "An overconfident model may output p=0.95 for cases that are only 60% correct.\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook:\n",
    "1. Measures raw calibration (ECE, reliability diagram)\n",
    "2. Applies **Temperature Scaling** (parametric, fast)\n",
    "3. Applies **Isotonic Regression** (non-parametric, flexible)\n",
    "4. Compares all three and selects the best method\n",
    "5. Checks overconfidence (extreme probability shrinkage after scaling)\n",
    "6. Re-optimises the decision threshold after calibration\n",
    "7. Defines and validates the **3-band triage confidence system**\n",
    "8. Reports ECE at high-confidence band (prob > 0.8)\n",
    "9. Saves calibration parameters for use in the report generator\n",
    "\n",
    "### Calibration circularity caveat\n",
    "> **Note:** Temperature scaling and isotonic regression are both fitted and evaluated\n",
    "> on the same validation set. This means **reported post-calibration ECE is slightly\n",
    "> optimistic**. In a production setting, a held-out calibration set should be used.\n",
    "> However, with 100K+ validation samples, the optimism is minimal.\n",
    ">\n",
    "> **Isotonic regression is especially affected:** being non-parametric, it can\n",
    "> perfectly memorise the calibration mapping, yielding ECE ≈ 0 on the training set.\n",
    "> To get an honest estimate, we report **5-fold cross-validated isotonic ECE**.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Slice-level calibration caveat\n",
    "> **Note:** Calibration is performed at the **slice level**. In deployment, predictions\n",
    "> are typically aggregated to the **patient level** (e.g., via max-pooling). Patient-level\n",
    "> aggregation changes the probability distribution — max-pooling inflates probabilities,\n",
    "> so slice-level calibration does **not** directly transfer. A patient-level calibration\n",
    "> step would be needed in production.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Required inputs\n",
    "- NB02 output: `manifest.csv` + `cache/` NPY arrays + `normalization_stats.json`\n",
    "- NB03 output: `best_model.pth`, `checkpoint.pth`"
   ]
  },
